" Cash Or Car ? 

" - For Company Car Drivers . 

From the 6th April 2002 , reforms proposed by the Chancellor relating to company car taxation will be introduced . 

' BIK ' ( The Benefit In Kind ) charge for company cars registered from 1st January 1998 will be calculated as a percentage of the cars price and linked to the vehicles C02 emissions . 

This C02 figure for the vehicle will remain unchanged for its entire life . 

Due to these changes of company car benefit in kind taxation , more and more people are being offered the chance to take cash instead of a company car . 

Guys offer a complete solution for company car drivers wanting to opt out of their company car schemes . 

Please Telephone or e-mail Ross Guy for further details . 

